<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--HalloweenRumors     11-02 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Halloween Rumors,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rumors of Satanic Sacrifices Cause Youngsters to Be Pulled from School</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUTLER, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rumors of planned satanic cult sacrifices of
children kept about 25 percent of Taylor County Elementary School
pupils home on Halloween, authorities said.
   Attendance was back to normal Wednesday.
   ``This morning I think a lot of people are looking back and are
embarrassed with themselves,'' school Superintendent Norman Carter
said. ``At least I hope so.''
   Carter said a rumor apparently started in nearby Fort Valley,
where many Butler residents work, that 12 black cats had been
sacrificed on the Butler town square.
   ``And from there it just got out of hand,'' Carter said, until
the rumor grew to include plans for kidnapping and sacrificing
children on Halloween.
   He said about 175 parents kept their children out of the
elementary school Tuesday _ about one-fourth of the school's
students. While the school administration discounted the rumors, he
said, security was increased as a precaution.
</TEXT>
