<TEXT>
   A court Thursday ordered an Istanbul daily
newspaper to pay the equivalent of $8,700 in damages for insulting
President-elect Turgut Ozal's family in a series published in May.
   The court said the articles in the newspaper Sabah defamed Ozal
and his wife, Semra.
