<HEAD>Air Force Plane Crashes Into Beer Warehouse; Pilot Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An air force training aircraft
crashed into a beer warehouse in southern Brazil on Thursday, and
the pilot was killed after ejecting from the plane, officials said.
   The twin-engine Brazilian Tucano plane crashed shortly after
takeoff from the Cindacta-2 air force base in the southern city of
Curitiba, 520 miles southwest of Rio, said Sgt. Edilson Jose
Tavares.
   ``His engines stopped, all I heard was a whistling overhead,''
said Arnaldo Lima, an employee at the warehouse. ``Then it smashed
