<HEAD>Bush to Visit His 88-Year-Old Mother Sunday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush will visit his mother, Dorothy
Walker Bush, at her Greenwich, Conn., home on Sunday, the White
House said Thursday.
   Mrs. Bush, 88, spent a week in the hospital in September in a
bout with pneumonia.
   Bush and his wife, Barbara, will stop in Connecticut en route
back to Washington after attending a ceremony earlier Sunday at
Phillips Academy in Andover, Mass., the prep school he was
