<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Aashish Khan, a master of Indian
classical music who has performed with George Harrison and Eric
Clapton, will raise money for a performing arts center with benefit
concerts Friday and Saturday.
   Khan, the nephew of famed sitar player Ravi Shankar, teaches
vocal and instrumental music at the Center for the Performing Arts
of India in east Fort Worth, which will receive proceeds from the
concerts.
   Khan said he and Shankar learned music at the feet of Khan's
grandfather, Allauddin Khan. Shankar and Khan worked together to
compose the score for the movie ``Ghandi.''
   Because there are few written scores of Indian music, most of it
is passed on personally from teacher to student, Khan said.
   ``This music has so much depth, it will never die,'' he said.
