<HEAD>Knock, Knock. Caiman. Reptiles Greet Apartment Manager</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KIRKWOOD, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Apartment manager Joe Hart had a hunch it
wasn't going to be a routine apartment inspection when he found a
caiman in the bathroom. The poisonous snake in the closet confirmed
his suspicions.
   Hart says he usually expects to find a few unwanted items left
by departing tenants.
   ``A cat, a dog, a canary, that's one thing ...,'' Hart said
after finding a 4-foot, 50-pound caiman _ an alligator relative _
wrapped around the toilet in the bathroom and a 3-foot cottonmouth
snake in an aquarium in the closet.
   ``I went in the bathroom and started to reach down to turn off
the water and I saw the tail and then the head and got out of
there,'' said Hart, who manages Aurora Apartments.
   Humane Society employees removed the pets Wednesday.
