   Construction spending was unchanged in
September after surging in August, the government said in another
report reflecting continued weakness in that segment of the economy.
   The Commerce Department said Wednesday that residential,
non-residential and government construction spending totaled a
seasonally adjusted annual rate of $415.6 billion in September
after jumping 1.5 percent in August, following declines of 1.8
percent in July and 0.8 percent in June.
