halt program trading when share prices drop too rapidly.
   Phelan, who testified Wednesday at a closed session of a House
Commerce subcommittee, said in earlier interviews that if left
unchecked, price volatility could destroy the stock market.
   Program trading, the computerized trading strategy linking the
stock and stock-index futures markets, has been blamed for
exaggerating recent sharp declines. Six major Wall Street firms
have either abandoned or reduced such trading in the last week.
</TEXT>
