<HEAD>Akron Beacon Journal Gets New Publisher</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: also on general news wires.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Christopher Harte, a member of the Texas
newspaper family that heads Harte-Hanks Communications Inc., has
been named publisher of Akron's Beacon Journal.
   Harte, president and publisher of the Centre Daily Times of
State College, Pa., since 1986, succeeds John McMillion, who
retires Jan. 1.
   Harte, 41, worked in the San Antonio-based family business as a
copy boy and photographer as a youth but later struck out on his
own.
   He joined Knight-Ridder Inc., parent of the Beacon Journal and
the Centre Daily Times, when he moved to the Miami Herald in 1983.
He worked there in both the news and business areas.
   A Stanford University graduate, Harte received a master's in
business administration from the University of Texas while
reporting for The Associated Press.
