   A good many Wall Streeters believe profits and dividends may
suffer further this winter, even if the economy is able to achieve
a ``soft landing'' rather than any severe slump.
   Uneasiness on that score was heightened today when Compaq
Computer projected lower fourth-quarter profits. Compaq shares
tumbled 18 to 88.
   Among other leading computer and technology issues, Computer
Associates International dropped ~ to 11|; International Business
Machines 2 to 96}; Hewlett-Packard 2 to 44{, and Microsoft 4| to
77{ in the over-the-counter market.
   UAL dropped 1 to 176 after trading briefly above 180 following
word late Wednesday that Reliance Group sought clearance to
increase its interest in the company to more than 15 percent.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
2.02 to 186.82. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was down 1.08 at 371.06.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 110.86 million shares with two
hours to go.
