<HEAD>Production Rises This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
223,128 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
219,590, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 244,048 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 144,506 cars this week,
compared with 146,148 a week ago and 157,360 in the same week in
1988.
