compared with last week's 73,442 and last year's 86,688.
   Canadian automakers were to build 26,678 cars this week, up from
23,691 a week ago and from last year's 20,870.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,628,
compared with 19,820 a week ago and 21,421 in the same week last
year.
